<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-13-0234 </DOCNO><TEXT>Nuclear plant performance, in terms of safety, reliability, output andcosts, can be influenced by implementation of recommendations and resolutionof findings contained in third party audits and reviews. The third partiesinvolved in auditing and reviewing Philadelphia Electric Company's nuclearplant operations are the following: 1) Nuclear Regulatory Commission(NRC); 2) Institute of Nuclear Power Operations (INPO); 3) American NuclearInsurers (ANI); 4) Management consultants Pennsylvania Public UtilityCommission (PUC). This article discusses what each of these groups isresponsible for during their audits and reviews.</TEXT></DOC>